description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;- Have you considered joining a friendly team in the glorious West Country? Situated on the beautiful South West coast, Plymouth boasts many local Heritage sites and areas of ‘outstanding natural interest’. At University Plymouth Hospitals, we recognise that work is only a part of your life - and the Trust is ideally located for walking, cycling, sailing and many other indoor and outdoor pursuits. Plymouth also has good transport links to the rest of the UK and Europe via road, rail and sea. With an amazing quality of life, stunning waterfront location, buzzing city centre, fascinating maritime history, there is quite simply nowhere better to live, work and play than Plymouth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vocation&lt;/strong&gt;- University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust is the largest hospital trust in the south west peninsula, providing comprehensive secondary and tertiary healthcare. Our geography gives us a secondary care catchment population of 450,000 with a wider peninsula population of almost 2,000,000 people who can access our specialist services. This is all done with a key focus on care, enabling us to be rated as Outstanding for Care by the CQC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt;- As a teaching hospital, we provide comprehensive training and education for a wide range of healthcare professionals. We support the Universities of Plymouth and Exeter in the delivery of courses for the Faculty of Health and Social Work, for newly qualified, Master’s and further. We are able to provide you with training and opportunities which will help you to develop your future career including promotion prospects, apprenticeships and much more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for Staff Nurses in a variety of specialisms across the Trust, who are highly motivated and enthusiastic about providing outstanding care. University Hospitals Plymouth can offer you a friendly and social atmosphere with a forward thinking and progressive attitude to the changing face of the NHS. If you join our Trust you will benefit from a well-established appraisal scheme, in-service training, encouragement with CPD and excellent senior and peer support. Helping you to plan and work your future career goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are interested in joining our #onebigteam to progress or start your career at UHP, we would love to hear from you – we have many opportunities above Band 5 available too.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Relocation packages may be offered, dependent on specialism and experience.*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please apply today, or feel free to contact the Recruitment Team at plh-tr.recruitment-team@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust core values are ‘Put patients first’, Take ownership’, ‘Respect others’, ‘Be positive’ and &#39;Listen, Learn &amp; Improve&#39;. If you agree that these values should be integral to your work, then University Plymouth Hospitals NHS Trust has much to offer you.&lt;/p&gt;
